cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.COM
Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the optimization of limited feedback in a multi-user spatial multiplexing system, which involves quantization of channel state information. This falls under the purview of information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the design of a multiple-antenna base-station serving multiple single-antenna users, which involves networking and internet architecture.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper formulates an optimization problem for minimizing the average transmission power subject to users' target SINR and outage probability constraints, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the transmission of multiple streams of data to multiple users, which is a common scenario in multimedia applications.
5. cs.COM (Computational Complexity) - The paper develops an optimization framework using approximate analytical closed-form solutions, which involves computational complexity.
